<br>
His little voice told him so, even started to scream it at him. The little voice told had many good points, but he was soon gagged and taken off to the recesses of Solufein's subconciousness.<br>
<br>
It was midnight in Freeport, and Solufein was sneaking into the Sisters Guildhall.<br>
<br>
He had fallen asleep on the boat and had ended up sailing back and forth between Faydwer and Antonica a few times already before waking up. He had stood up Krystarn and also left his Brother Wardenn to hunt without him.<br>
<br>
Solufein had arrived at the docks of Freeport again, exhausted and feeling shameful. As usual when he was in the area he was planning to head off into the Commonlands to make his camp in a Kodiak cave he commonly used when in the area. It was then that Solufein's foolish thought process kicked in. The Sisters Guildhall was in Freeport...Krystarn might be there, and do you really want to wake up with 600 pounds of smelly Kodiak making it's bed on top of you?<br>
<br>
So it was, that Solufein found himself garbed in black leathers, sneaking as quietly as a whisper through the dormatory of the Sisters Guildhall.<br>
<br>
He sniffed the air as he crept, catching familiar scents in the air. Nysa was here..she commonly smelled of holy oils and incense. Mirabor smelled of many different herbs and...Krystarn...who smelled of the seabreeze off of the Ocean of Tears.<br>
<br>
He found her room and found the door unlocked. Easing the door open, he cast a quick spell to dispell any magical wards and crept in, shutting the door silently behind him. He stood there for many moments unmoving, assuring that her breathing was regular and that she was truely asleep.<br>
<br>
When he was certain, he crept  over and knelt at the side of her bed. He gazed upon her sleeping face and smiled. She looked just as beatiful as ever, her face was serene and peaceful, her mouth was open a bit and he could see a line of drool trailing down her cheek which made his smile widen. She shifted a little, smiling and placing her hand near her face. He looked upon the glowing velium ring he had given her.<br>
<br>
He had originally intended the ring to be an engagement ring, for Solufein, ever impulsive, had asked for her hand in marriage. She had been afraid, it was then that she pointed out something that Solufein had neglected to realize. He was 145 years old, nearing 146 in a couple days, while she was barely 20. Solufein was still young for an elf, but he had been around during the time of Krystarn's grandparents, and that unnerved her. She had said no to his proposal, and feared him angry, but Solufein could never be angry with her. He kissed her tenderly, and bid her take the ring as a symbol of his love for her.<br>
<br>
Wardenn had once pointed out something that Solufein had come to realize lately,  now that he knew he truely loved Krystarn. He would not age, and she would begin to wither away before him. More and more he realized that he wished Krystarn had his longevity, or that he could give up his long life to live his days out with the woman he so deeply loved.<br>
<br>
He warded these thoughts away, best to live in the present, and not dwell on the future. He looked upon Krystarn lovingly and stroked her warm cheek. She smiled slightly under his touch yet remained asleep. Solufein turned away briefly to remove something from his pack, a bundle of Marr Cherries he had gathered for her on Sister Isle. He placed them in a bowl on the table in her room, and onced more turned to face her sleeping form.<br>
<br>
The little impulsive voice spoke to him again and he found himself stripping off most of his black leather clothing and tossing it to the floor. Clad only in his breeches, Solufein lifted the covers and eased himself into the bed with Krystarn ever so carefully. He worked his arms in an embrace around her and kissed her open mouth softly. <br>
<br>
&quot; I love you Krystarn...more than anything in the world.&quot; Solufein whispered softly. She cooed softly and snuggled into a more comfortable position in his arms. Solufein held her long into the night before sleep finally overtook him<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
