<br>
Looking back to the city, I wonder how long it will take Solufein to wake up.  He startled me this morning when I woke up in his arms… it was so comfortable though… so warm.  I know he will find me, he is good at that tracking stuff and I wasn’t very quiet when I left though I tried my best so he could sleep longer.<br>
<br>
I look at the ring he gave me, it so pretty and it feels so good to have on my finger.  I sigh.  Solufein is so different than what I am used to here.  I wish mother where here now…<br>
<br>
Looking out over the sea I shudder.  I hate the sea, I hate it.  I wrap my arms around my knees and wait for the sun to rise.<br>
 <p><B>Krystarn</B><BR>
