<br>
He snuck back out of the Hall and let his feet take him to the desert. He had not bothered to dress himself, the gentle sea breeze combined with the searing desert wind felt good on his bare chest and back.<br>
<br>
Perhaps unconcsiously, his walk had taken him to the outskirts of the barbarian fishing village. looking up, he saw Krystarn sitting on the shore.<br>
<br>
He quietly walked up to her, sitting down and wrapping his arms around her. He did not feel the need for words, he simply held her close and nuzzled her neck as the sun rose over the tranquil sea.<br>
