<br>
“Once, I got caught by some of the Militia.  I think they knew me cause they argued with my dad over the fine.  I guess he paid cause they let me go finally.  I was so scared, they kept me under the arena and it smelled awful.  There were people in some other cells, they looked so hurt and some would just lay there.  The guards ignored me until my dad showed up, then they yelled at me a few times before he walked in.”<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Leaning into Solufein more I close my eyes.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
“I am rambling, my father said my mother did it all the time and that’s where I got it.” <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Trying to sound like a man I say in my mock-my-dad-voice.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  “Soldiers don’t talk unless ordered to, keep that in mind missy when your training starts.”<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    I start talking in my normal voice again.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
“When my mother… died, he started my training among the Knights of Marr.  I was never very good at fighting with a sword and shield.  It didn’t deter him though and so my training went on.  He pulled out old books on tactics and magic.  How to deal with certain spells, what works best when… how to identify spells when they are cast and the best counter for them.”<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   I pause for a bit… not sure how to continue.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
“Solufein, I think what I am saying is… I don’t know what to do now, how to act.  I can go to High Hold and help fight the goblins in the tunnels without really thinking, I just do what I am expected to do.  I can sit with Omi in that damn swamp and deal with Spectres without fear… I even don’t mind that stupid dead thing that Kel carries with him all the time (ooc – shameless plug - lol) but when you walk into the room… I panic.”  <br>
 <p><B>Krystarn</B><BR>
Cleric of Mithaniel Marr
<BR>"Life is simple, if you are nice to your cleric."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ufalinoralastrarran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Falinor Alastrarran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#660000>(9/25/02 11:47:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=299.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.game-revolution.com/misc/staff/aawhite.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_heartbeating.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Love for Her</span><hr size=1> Solufein leans her down into the sand and kisses her gently, ignoring the looks of the fishermen.<br>
<br>
&quot;Krystarn, you know I don't expect you to act any certain way with me. I am happy just being with you, holding you brings a center to my life that I have never had before.&quot;<br>
<br>
Solufein strokes her hair and smiles, keeping his gaze locked with hers.<br>
<br>
&quot;I cannot tell you how to act my love, nobody can learn how to love another person.. but Krystarn, I know that I love you, more than anything in my life. I want to be with you, and that is enough for me...&quot;<br>
<br>
Solufein remains still, gazing at her and stroking her cheek, as the surf sprays them with a fine mist. <p><left>
