<br>
He had rather pleasant memories from the day...laying together wrapped up in her warm cloak on the windswept tundra of the Great Divide, her kisses, her smile as she ran her hands through his bluish gray hair. Sitting on the railing at the docks at Freeport, speaking of their pasts, closing their eyes and hugging close while the breeze blew in from the Ocean of Tears.<br>
<br>
They had eventualy gone to the wedding of Jaranna to Vivienne and Daninglight. Solufein had originonally had no intention of attending the unholy ceremony, but Krystarn had promised to her Sister that she would go. Solufein went to protect Krystarn. Solufein had sat their stoicly, not reacting to it all, he simply held Krystarn close. Everything had been fine until Mizzery began the bloodletting ceremony. He had not noticed it at first, a slight tingling in his Teir'dal blood. Then his eyes began to glow with a lavander fire, he had felt the dark magic of the Hate Prince in the ceremony. He had tried not to show it, though he could not help but grip Krystarn tighter and graze her shoulder with his teeth, which he quickly covered with a kiss.<br>
<br>
The ceremony had gone interrupted and Solufein and Krystarn had both left, he hoped she had not noticed his burning eyes as they sailed back to the Sisters Hall.<br>
Exhausted, they had both settled into slumber rather quickly, sharing warmth long into the night.<br>
<br>
The moon reflected the flickering lavender flame in Solufein's eyes still, he touched the scars on his neck for a moment and remembered the one who had left those marks. Solufein kissed Krystarn's shoulder and buried his face to sleep in her soft auburn tresses.<br>
